## Implementation Plan

### Problem
4 open Dependabot alerts on transitive dependencies:
- #116 (High): rollup 4.54.0 in root — CVE-2026-27606 arbitrary file write via path traversal
- #115 (High): rollup 4.54.0 in docs — same CVE
- #118 (High): svgo 4.0.0 in docs — CVE-2026-29074 Billion Laughs DoS via DOCTYPE entity expansion
- #119 (Low): @tootallnate/once 2.0.0 in root — CVE-2026-3449 promise hang after AbortSignal abort

### Approach
All 4 are transitive dependencies that cannot be directly bumped. Used pnpm overrides
(consistent with existing pattern for fast-xml-parser, minimatch, ajv, h3, devalue).

### Dependency Chains
- rollup (root): vitest → vite → rollup
- rollup (docs): astro → vite → rollup
- svgo (docs): astro → svgo
- @tootallnate/once (root): @google-cloud/storage → teeny-request → http-proxy-agent@5 → @tootallnate/once

### Risk Assessment
- rollup >=4.59.0: Low risk — patch within same minor, vite 6/7 both support rollup 4.x
- svgo >=4.0.1: Very low risk — patch release
- @tootallnate/once >=3.0.1: Low-Medium — major version jump (2→3), but dev-only dep in deprecated chain (http-proxy-agent@5). Even teeny-request@10 still pins http-proxy-agent@^5, so no upstream fix available.

### Verification
- Build: passes
- Tests: 898/898 pass (6 e2e failures are pre-existing EDITOR env issue)
- pnpm why: all 4 packages resolved to patched versions
